# Project: RISC-V SoC with INT8 Systolic Array Accelerator
# Target: Zynq-7020 (Digilent Zybo Z7-20 or Arty Z7-20)
# Toolchain: Vivado 2023.x, Verilator, SymbiYosys, ModelSim
# HDL: SystemVerilog exclusively (no VHDL, no plain Verilog)

---

## Project Overview

I am building a complete SoC in SystemVerilog targeting a Xilinx Zynq-7020 FPGA 
as a portfolio project for ASIC/FPGA new grad job applications. The system consists 
of three major components that will be integrated together:

1. A 5-stage pipelined RISC-V RV32IM CPU implemented in the Zynq PL fabric
2. An INT8 8x8 systolic array matrix multiply accelerator in the Zynq PL fabric
3. AXI4-Lite and AXI4-Stream interconnect allowing the Zynq PS (ARM Cortex-A9) 
   to orchestrate the accelerator

The project also includes:
- A UVM testbench for the accelerator targeting >90% functional coverage
- SymbiYosys formal verification for the AXI slave and CPU hazard unit
- Bare-metal C software running on the PS side to drive and benchmark the accelerator
- Full documentation including timing reports, utilization reports, and block diagrams

This is NOT a toy project. Every design decision should reflect industry best 
practices for RTL design. Code must be synthesizable unless explicitly in a 
testbench context.

