## Phase 2: INT8 Systolic Array Accelerator

### Architecture Specification

Implement an NxN systolic array (default N=8, parameterized as ARRAY_SIZE).

Dataflow: Weight-stationary
- Weights are preloaded into each PE and held stationary
- Input activations flow left-to-right across rows
- Partial sums flow top-to-bottom through columns
- Each PE computes: acc += weight * input (8-bit multiply, 32-bit accumulate)

### Processing Element (pe.sv)
Each PE contains:
- 8-bit weight register (loaded during weight-loading phase)
- 8-bit input register (loaded from left neighbor or input buffer)
- 32-bit accumulator register
- Computation: acc_r <= acc_r + (weight_r * data_in) on each clock
- Outputs: data_out (passes input to right neighbor), acc_out (to south neighbor)
- Control ports: load_weight, clear_acc, output_valid
- Pipeline the multiply-accumulate to meet timing (register the product)

### PE Array (pe_array.sv)
- Instantiate ARRAY_SIZE x ARRAY_SIZE PEs
- Wire correctly for weight-stationary systolic dataflow:
  - pe[i][j].data_out → pe[i][j+1].data_in (left to right)
  - pe[i][j].acc_out → pe[i+1][j].acc_in (top to bottom)
  - pe[0][j] inputs connect to input_buffer row j
  - pe[i][ARRAY_SIZE-1].acc_out connects to output_buffer column i
- Generate block for instantiation — do not manually instantiate 64 PEs
- Tie-off boundary conditions explicitly (first column acc_in = 0)

### Memory Architecture
Weight buffer:
  - Dual-port BRAM, 8-bit wide, depth = ARRAY_SIZE * ARRAY_SIZE (64 entries)
  - Written via AXI4-Lite interface during weight-loading phase
  - Read port connects directly to PE array during compute phase

Input buffer:
  - Dual-port BRAM, 8-bit wide, depth = ARRAY_SIZE * ARRAY_SIZE (64 entries)
  - Written via AXI4-Stream interface for streaming inputs
  - Read port streams into PE array row inputs during compute phase

Output buffer:
  - Registers (not BRAM), 32-bit wide, ARRAY_SIZE entries
  - Captures final accumulator outputs from bottom row of PE array
  - Read via AXI4-Lite interface after compute completes

### Control FSM (control_fsm.sv)
States (use enum typedef in package):
  IDLE → LOAD_WEIGHTS → CLEAR_ACC → COMPUTE → OUTPUT_VALID → IDLE

Transitions:
  IDLE: wait for start pulse from AXI control register
  LOAD_WEIGHTS: shift weights into PE array row by row (ARRAY_SIZE cycles)
  CLEAR_ACC: broadcast clear_acc to all PEs (1 cycle)
  COMPUTE: stream inputs through array (ARRAY_SIZE + ARRAY_SIZE - 1 cycles for 
           full systolic fill), assert compute_done when last output valid
  OUTPUT_VALID: assert output_valid, wait for read_done from AXI slave
  IDLE: deassert everything, ready for next transaction

### Performance Target
- Achieve timing closure at ≥125MHz on Zynq-7020
- DSP48 inference: PE multipliers must map to DSP48 slices
  (use (* use_dsp = "yes" *) synthesis attribute)
- Target utilization for accelerator: ~64 DSP48s, ~4 BRAMs, <5,000 LUTs

---

## Phase 3: AXI4 Integration

### Memory Map
Implement this exact memory map in the AXI4-Lite slave:

Base address: 0x4000_0000 (connected to Zynq AXI_GP0 port)

Offset 0x000 — CTRL register (W)
  bit[0]: start (write 1 to begin computation, auto-clears)
  bit[1]: reset accelerator (write 1, auto-clears)

Offset 0x004 — STATUS register (R)
  bit[0]: done (1 = computation complete, results readable)
  bit[1]: busy (1 = computation in progress)
  bit[2]: error (1 = AXI protocol violation detected)

Offset 0x008 — CONFIG register (RW)
  bits[7:0]: matrix_size (default 8)

Offset 0x100-0x13F — WEIGHT_BUFFER (W) — 64 bytes, one per PE weight

Offset 0x200-0x23F — OUTPUT_BUFFER (R) — 32 bytes, 8x 32-bit results

### AXI4-Lite Slave (axi4_lite_slave.sv)
Implement full AXI4-Lite slave protocol:
- All 5 channels: AW, W, B, AR, R
- VALID/READY handshake on every channel — never drop VALID once asserted
  until READY is seen (this is the most commonly violated AXI rule)
- BRESP and RRESP: return OKAY (2'b00) on success, SLVERR (2'b10) on 
  invalid address
- Single outstanding transaction only (no out-of-order support needed)
- Include SVA assertions inline to verify handshake protocol is never violated:
  // VALID must not deassert without a READY
  assert property (@(posedge clk) disable iff (!rst_n)
    s_axi_awvalid && !s_axi_awready |=> s_axi_awvalid);

### AXI4-Stream Input Interface (axi4_stream_input.sv)
- Accepts streaming input matrix data from PS side
- TDATA: 8-bit (one element per beat)
- TVALID/TREADY handshake
- TLAST: asserted on final element of input matrix
- Writes directly into input_buffer BRAM
- Asserts stream_done to control FSM when TLAST received

