## Phase 5: Formal Verification

### SymbiYosys Setup
Create .sby configuration files for two targets:

1. formal/axi_slave.sby — Verify AXI4-Lite slave protocol
   Prove these properties:
   - AWVALID never drops without AWREADY (write address channel)
   - WVALID never drops without WREADY (write data channel)  
   - ARVALID never drops without ARREADY (read address channel)
   - RVALID is only asserted after a valid ARVALID/ARREADY handshake
   - BRESP is always OKAY or SLVERR, never an undefined value
   Use bounded model checking, depth = 20 cycles

2. formal/hazard_unit.sby — Verify CPU hazard detection
   Prove these properties:
   - If EX stage has a load instruction and ID stage reads the same register,
     a stall is always generated
   - A forwarding path is always selected when a RAW hazard exists
     without a load-use dependency
   - No instruction ever reads a stale register value (the key safety property)
   Use bounded model checking, depth = 15 cycles

