## Phase 6: Bare-Metal Software (PS Side)

### accel_driver.c
Write a complete bare-metal C driver targeting the ARM Cortex-A9 PS:

#define ACCEL_BASE      0x40000000
#define CTRL_OFFSET     0x000
#define STATUS_OFFSET   0x004
#define WEIGHT_OFFSET   0x100
#define OUTPUT_OFFSET   0x200

Functions to implement:
  void accel_reset(void);
  void accel_load_weights(uint8_t weights[8][8]);
  void accel_stream_inputs(uint8_t inputs[8][8]);  // via AXI-Stream
  void accel_start(void);
  int  accel_wait_done(uint32_t timeout_cycles);   // returns 0 on timeout
  void accel_read_outputs(uint32_t outputs[8]);
  void accel_matmul(uint8_t w[8][8], uint8_t in[8][8], uint32_t out[8][8]);

Benchmarking main():
  - Implement a software reference matrix multiply on the ARM
  - Time it using the ARM cycle counter (PMCCNTR)
  - Run the same matrix on the accelerator
  - Time the full round-trip including AXI transactions
  - Print both times over UART
  - Assert results match to verify correctness
  - Calculate and print speedup ratio

---

## Synthesis and Timing Constraints (zybo_z7.xdc)

Include these constraints:
  # Primary clock
  create_clock -period 8.000 -name clk [get_ports clk]
  
  # False paths on resets
  set_false_path -from [get_ports rst_n]
  
  # DSP48 timing exception for pipelined multipliers
  set_multicycle_path -setup 2 -from [get_cells */pe_array/*] \
    -through [get_pins */DSP48*]

Target: No setup or hold violations at 125MHz after implementation.

