## What To Build First (Start Here)

Begin with these files in this exact order:

1. rtl/cpu/riscv_pkg.sv
   - Define all pipeline stage structs as packed structs
   - Define instruction decode enums (opcode_t, funct3_t, funct7_t)
   - Define forwarding select enums
   - All subsequent CPU files import this package

2. rtl/cpu/alu.sv
   - Inputs: alu_op (from enum), a, b (32-bit)
   - Output: result (32-bit), zero flag, overflow flag
   - Operations: ADD, SUB, AND, OR, XOR, SLL, SRL, SRA, SLT, SLTU
   - Purely combinational (always_comb only)
   - This is the easiest module and validates your toolchain works

3. rtl/cpu/regfile.sv
   - 32x32-bit register file
   - x0 hardwired to zero (never write)
   - Two async read ports, one sync write port
   - Forwarding-aware: if write address == read address and write enable,
     return write data directly (bypass)

4. tb/sim/alu_tb.sv
   - Exhaustive directed tests for all ALU operations
   - Test every edge case: overflow, zero result, shift by 0, shift by 31
   - This is your first Verilator simulation target

Do not start the systolic array or AXI work until the CPU pipeline is 
simulating correctly with passing assembly tests. Build in order.

