## Context For AI Assistance

When I ask you to implement a module, always:
1. Write the complete module, not a skeleton
2. Follow every coding standard listed above without being reminded
3. Add inline comments explaining non-obvious design decisions
4. Flag any timing or synthesis concerns explicitly
5. Suggest the testbench stimulus needed to verify the module
6. Note if a design decision deviates from industry practice and why

When I ask you to debug RTL:
1. Check for common synthesis pitfalls first (latches, multiple drivers)
2. Check reset behavior explicitly
3. Check for off-by-one errors in pipeline register timing
4. Suggest specific waveform signals to probe to diagnose the issue

When I ask about AXI:
1. Always reference the specific channel (AW/W/B/AR/R) by name
2. Always confirm VALID/READY handshake semantics before implementing
3. Flag any potential deadlock conditions

My target board is a Digilent Zybo Z7-20 with a Zynq-7020.
My toolchain is Vivado 2023.x and Verilator 5.x.
My HDL is SystemVerilog (IEEE 1800-2017).
I am building this as a portfolio project for FPGA/ASIC new grad job applications.
Correctness and synthesis quality matter more than development speed.